President Donald J. Trump has designated a Presidential Delegation to attend the second Inauguration of President Nana Addo Dankwa Akufo-Addo of Ghana. The delegation will be led by Dr. J. Peter Pham, the United States Special Envoy for the Sahel Region of Africa. Another member of the delegation is Stephanie S. Sullivan, the United States Ambassador to Ghana. The inauguration will take place on January 7, 2021, in Accra, Ghana.